@node Entry Paths and Calling Convention
@section Entry Paths and Calling Convention

VibeOS provides two ways for user mode to enter the kernel:

@itemize @bullet
@item @code{int $0x80} through IDT vector 128, and
@item amd64 @code{syscall} through the MSR-programmed fast path.
@end itemize

The main calling convention follows the Linux amd64 syscall ABI:

@itemize @bullet
@item syscall number in @code{rax},
@item arguments in @code{rdi}, @code{rsi}, @code{rdx}, @code{r10},
@code{r8}, and @code{r9}, and
@item return value in @code{rax}.
@end itemize

The dispatcher itself is a large switch over syscall numbers in
@file{kernel/src/syscall.c}.

