The shipped @file{/usr} mount is read-only, so mutating filesystem calls
currently fail there with @code{EROFS}; the ext2/ext3 backend and VFS paths are
implemented for read-write ext2 or ext3 mounts.

@node Descriptors and Devices
@section Descriptors, Polling, and Devices

Descriptor and multiplexing calls include:

@multitable @columnfractions .10 .20 .70
@headitem Nr @tab Name @tab Notes
@item 0 @tab @code{read} @tab Supports TTY, framebuffer, pipe, Unix-domain
socket, regular-file, and null descriptors.
@item 1 @tab @code{write} @tab Supports TTY, framebuffer, pipe, Unix-domain
socket, and null descriptors.
@item 7 @tab @code{poll} @tab Busy-wait implementation without a timer source.
@item 16 @tab @code{ioctl} @tab TTY and framebuffer-specific commands.
@item 19 @tab @code{readv} @tab Built on repeated @code{read}.
@item 20 @tab @code{writev} @tab Built on repeated @code{write}.
@item 22 @tab @code{pipe} @tab Equivalent to @code{pipe2} with zero flags.
@item 23 @tab @code{select} @tab Blocking scheduler-aware descriptor
multiplexing.
@item 32 @tab @code{dup} @tab Duplicate descriptor.
@item 33 @tab @code{dup2} @tab Duplicate to an exact descriptor.
@item 40 @tab @code{sendfile} @tab File-to-descriptor copy helper.
@item 41 @tab @code{socket} @tab Supports pathname @code{AF_UNIX}
@code{SOCK_STREAM} sockets plus limited @code{AF_INET} stream, datagram, and
raw ICMP sockets.
@item 42 @tab @code{connect} @tab Connects a Unix-domain stream socket to a
listening pathname endpoint, or records/connects an IPv4 remote endpoint for
@code{AF_INET} sockets.
@item 43 @tab @code{accept} @tab Accepts pending Unix-domain stream
connections.
@item 44 @tab @code{sendto} @tab Send path for Unix-domain stream sockets and
limited IPv4 TCP, UDP, and raw ICMP sockets.
@item 45 @tab @code{recvfrom} @tab Receive path for Unix-domain stream sockets
and limited IPv4 TCP, UDP, and raw ICMP sockets.
@item 46 @tab @code{sendmsg} @tab Vector send helper layered over
@code{sendto}; @code{AF_INET} data is flattened into one bounded packet buffer.
@item 47 @tab @code{recvmsg} @tab Vector receive helper layered over
@code{recvfrom}; control-message handling is not implemented.
@item 48 @tab @code{shutdown} @tab Read-side and write-side shutdown for
connected Unix-domain stream sockets, and write-side close for connected IPv4
