@item 270 @tab @code{pselect6} @tab Same scan model as @code{select}.
@item 288 @tab @code{accept4} @tab Accept path with nonblocking and
close-on-exec flags.
@item 292 @tab @code{dup3} @tab Implemented like exact descriptor duplication.
@item 293 @tab @code{pipe2} @tab Main pipe constructor; flags are currently
restricted.
@end multitable

The kernel understands TTY descriptors, @file{/dev/null}, a framebuffer
descriptor, directories, regular files, pipes, pathname
@code{AF_UNIX}/@code{SOCK_STREAM} sockets, and limited IPv4 sockets over the
in-tree network stack.  The IPv4 path currently covers ARP, DHCP configuration,
ICMP echo traffic, UDP datagrams, and client-side TCP streams; it is sufficient
for basic tools such as statically linked @code{wget}, but it is not a complete
Linux network stack.

